8edb			; Get a hexadecimal digit from the serial line. This routine blocks until 
8edb			; a valid character (0-9a-f) has been entered. A valid digit will be echoed 
8edb			; to the serial line interface. The lower 4 bits of A contain the value of  
8edb			; that particular digit. 
